-- GM to get 60 days funding for added restructuring: U.S. official
-- 
-- Mon Mar 30, 2009 2:22am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/03/30/us-gm-funding-sb-idUSTRE52T0FV20090330

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - A U.S. government official speaking to Reuters on condition of anonymity because the plans have not yet been announced: 

 * Says Obama Administration will fund General Motors for 60 days as it restructures, tries to develop viability plan * Says administration will work with Chrysler to try to develop automaker's proposed alliance with Fiat * Says Chrysler could receive up to $6 billion additional aid if Fiat alliance is completed * Says U.S. government gives Chrysler 30 days to complete Fiat alliance (Reporting by  John Crawley  and  Kevin Krolicki )